FBIS4-9425 "dreeu080_b_94001" FBIS-EEU-94-080 Daily Report 25 Apr 1994 BULGARIA Deputy Defense Minister Resigns Deputy Defense Minister Resigns AU2504135094 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 1300 GMT 25 Apr 94 AU2504135094 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network Bulgarian BFN [Text] After submitting his resignation, Deputy Minister of Defense Boyko Noev stated that recently intensified political pressure prevents him from implementing his duties. He hoped that the government, I quote, is able to overcome the difficult situation. [no reference to close of quotation as heard] On the other hand, according to a report from the Council of Ministers, [Defense] Minister Aleksandrov heard about his deputy's resignation from journalists.
